race.comment: TORQUE TO BE SURE (1) wasn't disgraced at Group 1 level before the spell and will find this assignment much more to his liking. Draws the inside alley and may run a big race while fresh. FORGOTTEN SPIRIT (6) strips fitter second-up from the break and gets the reliable Gollan/Jones combination. Worth serious consideration. SPIRIT OF BARTY (10) was a handy Sunny Coast winner on debut and winning rider Lang stays on top. Keep very safe. GUAC ON (2) has trialled since the fresh effort and has won second-up before so can progress.
